[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Identity and authentication are one of those things every app needs, but most developers don\'t really enjoy building. Ideally, you want an identity stack that is secure, flexible, reliable, and doesn\'t take weeks to assemble. Sure,'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'there are providers like Ozero, Octto, but they are all tightly controlled ecosystems with their own limitations. What many developers don\'t realize is that there is a fully open-source identity server that covers all the'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'essentials without locking you in. That server is AI Kratos. In this video, we\'ll look at what makes Kratos such a powerful choice and then I will walk you through how to use it to set up your own'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'identity stack. [music] It\'s going to be a lot of fun. So, let\'s dive into it. Oriratos is a very powerful identity management server that lets you'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'implement user management and authentication in a secure and straightforward way. It has all the features you might expect from an advanced identity provider. Different login flows, account activation, multiffactor authentication tools,'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'profile and session management and user recovery methods. And you can easily spin it up through a Docker image. It aims to be a backendon interface. So you can hook it up to any kind of'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'application or any kind of UI interface you are developing. But if you do need a readytouse UI solution for Kratos, there\'s also a library called AI elements which provides all the basic UI components for a complete login flow and'

[01:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you will see it in action later in this video. Another cool thing is that Kratos is very secure and GDPR compliant. It applies all the necessary security standards established by experts from'

[01:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'National Institute of Sciences, Internet Engineering Task Force, Microsoft Research, Google Research, Troy Hunt, and many others. And Kratos is just the core server. But if you\'re looking for a'

[01:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'really sophisticated bespoke solution for your own project, Kratos has other tools available that you can plug in like Hydra for OOTH 2 flows, Ketto for complex user permission structures,'

[02:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Polus for enterprise level SSO bridge, and Oathkeeper for an identity aware proxy. So as you can see, you can build a very very complex open-source identity stack with all these tools, but today'

[02:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'we\'re just going to be focusing on the basics. We\'re going to be building a simple Nex.js app that uses Kratos as the core server and we will also use AI elements to leverage their readyto-use UI components for our login flow. So'

